Parse a wastd_api_response of Encounter observations to tbl_df

Source: R/parse_encounterobservations.R
parse_encounterobservations.Rd

parse_encounterobservations(wastd_api_response, payload = "data")

Arguments

wastd_api_response

A wastd_api_response of turtle-nest-*, e.g. wastd_GET("turtle-nest-encounters")

payload

The parameter payload for wastd_parse.

Value

A tbl_df with non-repetitive columns of:

  • Encounter

  • Survey

  • Area

  • Site

  • Observation

Details

WAStD provides all subclasses of wastd.observations.observation together with their encounter (survey, site, area, reporter, observer) via its API as GeoJSON FeatureCollections.

This function acts as a generic parser for

  • "turtle-nest-hatchling-emergences"

  • "turtle-nest-hatchling-emergence-outliers"

  • "turtle-nest-hatchling-emergence-light-sources"

  • "turtle-nest-excavations"

  • "turtle-nest-tag-observations"

  • "turtle-nest-disturbance-observations"
